.TH "ASYNCDISPOSABLESTACK.USE" "3JS" "November 27, 2025" "JavaScript" "JavaScript Reference Manual"
.SH NAME
AsyncDisposableStack.use \- AsyncDisposableStack.prototype.use()
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]use()\f[B]\f[R] method of \f[CR]AsyncDisposableStack\f[R]
instances registers a value that implements the async disposable
protocol to the stack.
.PP
See \f[CR]DisposableStack.prototype.use()\f[R] for general information
about the \f[CR]use()\f[R] method.
.SH SYNTAX
.IP
.EX
use(value)
.EE
.SS Parameters
.TP
\f[B]value\f[R]
The value to register to the stack.
Must either contain a \f[CR][Symbol.asyncDispose]()\f[R] or
\f[CR][Symbol.dispose]()\f[R] method, or be \f[CR]null\f[R] or
\f[CR]undefined\f[R].
.SS Return value
The same \f[CR]value\f[R] that was passed in.
.SS Exceptions
.TP
\f[B]TypeError\f[R]
Thrown if \f[CR]value\f[R] is not \f[CR]null\f[R] or
\f[CR]undefined\f[R], and does not contain a
\f[CR][Symbol.asyncDispose]()\f[R] or \f[CR][Symbol.dispose]()\f[R]
method.
.TP
\f[B]ReferenceError\f[R]
Thrown if the stack is already disposed.
.SH EXAMPLES
.SS Using use()
This function reads a file (as a Node.js \c
.UR https://nodejs.org/api/fs.html#class-filehandle
\f[CR]FileHandle\f[R]
.UE \c
) and returns its contents.
The file handle is automatically closed when the function completes,
given that the \f[CR]FileHandle\f[R] class implements a
\f[CR][Symbol.asyncDispose]()\f[R] method that asynchronously closes the
file.
.IP
.EX
\f[B]async\f[R] \f[B]function\f[R] readFileContents(path) {
  \f[B]await\f[R] using disposer = \f[B]new\f[R] AsyncDisposableStack();
  \f[B]const\f[R] handle = disposer.use(\f[B]await\f[R] fs.open(path));
  \f[B]const\f[R] data = \f[B]await\f[R] handle.read();
  \f[B]return\f[R] data;
  \f[I]// The disposer is disposed here, which causes handle to be closed too\f[R]
}
.EE
